&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48843378</guid><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 09:52:13 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Show HN: Ved AI Voice Assistant</title><link>https://github.com/Krish6190/Ved-Test</link><description>&lt;p&gt;I built Ved because I wanted a fully offline, self hosted Jarvis for my house, that runs comfortably on everyday consumer hardware (specs 12GB VRAM GPU), without ruining system performance(multi modal).&lt;p&gt;Where I plan to take this next:&lt;p&gt;1)Server-client Architecture: I want to shift the heavy load off of ur main device onto a secondary central server where the heavy LLMS and lower models work without ruining ur personal machine.&lt;p&gt;2)Smart Home: I want to make small cheap mic/speaker endpoints (using small ups like Raspberry) allowing you to communicate with Ved without needing another appliance.&lt;p&gt;3)Remote Access: I am checking out ways to securely make Ved communicate with outside local networks for free.&lt;p&gt;I would love to hear from anyone who has worked on a multi room audio setup. What hardware or protocols you found had the lowest latency.&lt;p&gt;Please try it out and let me know if you have any feedback or suggestions :)&lt;/p&gt;
